<typeStatus id="9669884B3C301238C1AEFD75FDD3F069" box="[479,577,1855,1881]" pageId="14" pageNumber="163">syntypes</typeStatus>
consist of both males and females. I have selected one of the males, a specimen in good condition, to serve as 
<typeStatus id="9669884B3C301238C251FD28FD18F04C" box="[544,650,1890,1916]" pageId="14" pageNumber="163">lectotype</typeStatus>
, have labeled it such, and have imaged the habitus, male genitalia and labels of this specimen (
<figureCitation id="D1E92A6C3C301238C1DCFDCCFD99F090" box="[429,523,1926,1952]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1747,1772]" captionTargetBox="[215,1415,210,1685]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1435,193,1721]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 11. Hydrochus variabilis Knisch, habitus and male genitalia of lectotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557949/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="163">Figs. 11</figureCitation>
